Steps: {'Step 1': 'Remove the five exposed 7.9 mm phillips screws with the spudger. Punch through the warranty sticker with the spudger and remove the screw underneath.', 'Step 2': 'Remove the rubber feet with the screwdriver. Remove the screws that the rubber feet were covering.', 'Step 3': 'Lift up the cover gently. The tray is still connected to the base with wires.', 'Step 4': 'Remove the wires with tweezers by gently pulling on the base they are attached to.', 'Step 5': 'Use your hand to remove the small back cover.', 'Step 6': 'Remove the two 0.473" pan head screws as shown circled in the picture', 'Step 7': 'The screen should now detach from the main device. The screen will still be connected by the wires', 'Step 8': 'Remove the wires attached to the white base by using the tweezers', 'Step 9': 'Do the same with the wires attached to the black base.', 'Step 10': 'The screen should now be completely separated from the main device.'}

