Steps: {'Step 1': 'Remove the batteries from the mouse. Use a plastic opening tool to peel up the four mouse feet.', 'Step 2': 'Remove the five 5.5mm Phillips #00 screws found underneath the mouse feet.', 'Step 3': "Pull the top of the mouse off of the bottom half. There's a wire connecting the two halves. Unplug the programmable buttons from the motherboard.", 'Step 4': "Remove the three 5.5mm Phillips #00 screws holding the button assembly to the mouse. '''Do not''' remove any of the screws on the circuit board, only the ones holding the plastic assembly in place", 'Step 5': 'Disconnect the button board from the motherboard and remove the whole assembly.'}

