Steps: {'Step 1': 'Using a T5 Torx screwdriver, unscrew a total number of 23 screws located on the outside panel of the Surface Pro.', 'Step 2': 'Use the plastic opening tool or fingers to pry out the front camera.', 'Step 3': 'Lift the outside panel from the Surface Pro', 'Step 4': 'Use the T5 torx screw driver to unscrew the 6 T5 screws in the left and right outside metal panels Use the T2 torx screw driver to unscrew the 23 T2 screws on the left and right outside metal panels', 'Step 5': 'Pull out left and right metal panels with hands', 'Step 6': 'Pull out the orange charging port strip using tweezers', 'Step 7': 'Unscrew the two T5 torx screws located on each side of the charging port.', 'Step 8': 'Once you have unscrewed the charging port, you can gently pull it out with your hands.'}

