Steps: {'Step 1': 'Remove battery Turn Netbook upside down Unscrew all screws from the back of the pc Remove the back plate Unscrew metal cover on top of fan', 'Step 2': 'Gently lift the fan making sure not to drop dust into the motor of the fan below Clean fan blades Clean the fan house place the fan upside down so the metal pin points upwards', 'Step 3': 'Apply oil Apply one or two droplets of oil onto the metal pin Place it on the motor and make sure it rotates without problems In case there is still sounds coming from the fan when turned on, redo the cleaning and lubrication.', 'Step 4': 'Assemble everything and test'}

