Steps: {'Step 1': 'Remove the back cover with the opening tool to reveal the battery', 'Step 2': 'Now remove the battery and keep it somewhere safe for now', 'Step 3': 'Unscrew the nine screws shown with the Philips #0 screwdriver Be sure not to lose any screws', 'Step 4': 'You must detach and replace the entire motherboard the replace the charging port Slowly lift the motherboard up to pull it off the orange strip Pull slowly, you do not want to break this strip', 'Step 5': 'Due to the connector being sawdered on you must replace the whole mother boar so, insert your new motherboard Make sure you line it up correctly with the orange strip'}

