Steps: {'Step 1': 'Locate the button right above the F8 key.', 'Step 2': 'Use a spudger or plastic opening tool to push the button away from you.', 'Step 3': 'Insert the spudger under the keyboard and slide it along the length of the keyboard.', 'Step 4': 'Do not attempt to remove the keyboard. It is still attached to the laptop by a ribbon cable.', 'Step 5': 'Remove the ribbon cable from the connector.'}

