Steps: {'Step 1': 'Shut down the laptop and disconnect the power cord Failing to disconnect or shut down the laptop could result in damage to the laptop or a shock hazard. Turn the laptop over', 'Step 2': 'Remove the (6) visible 10mm T-7 screws Remove the (4) visible 6mm T-7 screws Use the blue plastic opening tool to carefully remove the rubber pad which covers the two remaining screws Remove the remaining (2) 10mm T-7 screws', 'Step 3': 'Carefully lift the cover upwards If the cover seems stuck use a spudger tool to pry the sides'}

